        "Notice how the derivative $f'(x) = 2x$ is negative when $x < 0$ (parabola going down), zero at $x = 0$ (the bottom of the parabola), and positive when $x > 0$ (parabola going up). The colored dots on the right plot correspond to the tangent points on the left.\n",
